This demo project requires meson >= 0.51 to `meson dist`, but afterwards can be
built from the archive using meson = 0.45.

To create the tarball:

    meson build
    meson dist -C build --no-tests --include-subprojects --formats=gztar
    scp build/meson-dist/mesondisttest-*.tar.gz ...

The archive should be copied to a system with older meson. Then:

    tar -xvzf mesondisttest-*.tar.gz
    cd mesondisttest-*
    meson build --wrap-mode=nodownload

If, on older meson, you try to configure a build from repo instead of tarball,
you'll most likely get an error:

    The Meson build system
    Version: 0.45.1
    Source dir: /home/woju/test-1.2.3.4
    Build dir: /home/woju/test-1.2.3.4/build
    Build type: native build
    Project name: test
    Native C compiler: ccache cc (gcc 7.5.0 "cc (Ubuntu 7.5.0-3ubuntu1~18.04) 7.5.0")
    Build machine cpu family: x86_64
    Build machine cpu: x86_64
    Using cJSON-1.7.12 from cache.
    Package does not require patch.

    Executing subproject cJSON-1.7.12.


    meson.build:5:0: ERROR: Missing Meson file in /home/woju/test-1.2.3.4/subprojects/cJSON-1.7.12/meson.build

    A full log can be found at /home/woju/test-1.2.3.4/build/meson-logs/meson-log.txt

This is because the wrap uses patch_directory=, available on meson >= 0.51.
